e Root Cause - UIC Individual Pre-Selection  4:30pm to 6:30pm, Friday, February 21  School of Public Health (Room B34 - basement), 1601 West Taylor  This phase of the selection process will identify UIC health professions students who can advance to the next selection phases, based on their participation in a lightning round of individual presentations.  To find out more about eligibility and the details of the UIC Individual Pre-Selection Presentation on Friday February 21, please carefully review the document  2020 CLARION - Finding the Root Cause - UIC Individual Pre-Selection Competition , and IHI's Finding the Root Cause Toolkit .  The UIC Individual selection presentation will include a 4 slide PowerPoint presentation, that will be presented in 5 minutes or less, and will highlight the root cause analysis, and recommendations to address the issues described under “The Event” (see below starting on page 3 of this guide ) . Your presentation must include all four of the elements from the IHI “5 Whys: Finding the Root Cause” guide :  Individual Presentations: Once you have submitted your RSVP for participation in the UIC 2020 Clarion Interprofessional Case Competition, you will be assigned a 5 minute presentation slot between 4:30pm to 6:30pm, Friday, February 21.  Submitting your Powerpoint Slides: You must submit your Powerpoint slides by 11:59pm, Thursday, February 20 in the upload link below. Note: Late submissions will not be accepted and will result in immediate elimination.  To register for the UIC Individual Pre-Selection competition on Friday, February 21 please RSVP below.      RSVP: Finding the Root Cause - UIC Individual Pre-Selection   Please RSVP to the UIC Individual Pre – Selection Clarion Presentation. The event will take place on Friday, February 21 from 4:30pm to 6:30pm at the School of Public Health, located at 1601 West Taylor, Room B34 (basement). If there are any questions, please email Ami Shah, Project Coordinator at ashah58@uic.edu .    